You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.

metadata.name: Hyper-Vasarely #16
metadata.description:
This work is a tribute to Victor Vasarely. 

The algorithm reproduces part of the visual grammar of certain works by the artist and extends the resources used in his works by incorporating new elements. Each work is defined by the superposition of 2 or 3 layers made up of a grid of figures: squares, circles or triangles, each of which can be filled or hollow. 

Each layer has an evolution gradient that affects its color, and that can also affect other parameters of the figures in the grid, such as size, transparency, rotation or displacement. There are at least 8 different types of gradients that can affect each of these parameters.

At the same time, each layer can be affected by a subdivision into sectors that make changes to shapes, gradients, colors and the rest of the parameters. These subdivisions can be in the form of checkerboards, in either vertical or horizontal halves, or within an internal section.

The combination between the number of layers, their resolution (number of rows and columns of the grid), the subdivisions of the layers, the figures that are applied to each subdivision, and the gradients applied to the colors, sizes, rotations , transparencies and offset, generates a combinatorial explosion that is difficult to measure, but that undoubtedly generates thousands of different configurations within this visual grammar.


​​[s] to save a screen capture (5000 x 5000)

metadata.name: Glimpse Of Draeconian Epidermis & Tapestry #147
metadata.description:
Discover the artistic style and bold fashion of your favorite Reptilian overlords, the *Draeconians*!

Those NFTs are pictures, sure, but more intricately they are *Glimpses* of what these magnificent scaled shapeshifters are able to create using their sophisticated *Epidermis* machinery.

Nevertheless, and as it is the case for some humans in our world, you'll probably notice eventually that more often than not, the output products are better suited to be used as *Tapestry* rather than clothes or skin...

Features:
- 42 palettes aka Pigmentore's Names
- 4 rendering techniques aka Workore's Names
- 5 types of patterns aka Designore's Tribes...
- ... which result into more than 40 different patterns aka Designore's Names
- 5 transformations aka Designore's Traits
- etc.

About me:
I am MaKRz, a creative coder and generative artist living in Lisbon area. I like to take inspiration in real life and nature (animals, landscapes, buildings) to start with a concept and eventually totally mess it up.
Check out @MaKRz666 on Twitter.

Made with p5js

metadata.description:

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes

metadata.name: chorégraphie #239
metadata.description:
… divided in two,
like the parent in sound and motion.
yet not exactly the same, I get …


chorégraphie explores the algorithmic characteristics of recursion in audiovisual form.

The algorithm performs a recursive split. At each split stage, space is divided into four different sized quadrants. Each split stage will eventually spawn an oscillator or a synthesizer representing the current properties of recursion in sound. The process is recursively repeated until a maximum recursion depth is reached or an early return condition is met.
Additionally, an initial motion funnction is randomly selected and propageted through the recursion, so that each recursive split stage with move depending on it’s split properties in combination with time.

Click into the piece to start the audio. Each piece can be seeded with a new initial configuration by pressing the ‘s’ key.

© 2022 — Guido Schmidt

Created with:
p5, tone, @thi.ng/color, random

metadata.name: Wild Paper Road #19
metadata.description: To get to Wild Paper you have to take Wild Paper Road.  This work introduces collectors to the Wild Paper series.  Hand-drawn art is combined with generative procedures to create amazing landscapes in a curious and compelling style.  Wild Paper Road combines these assets with perspective movement generating the illusion of traveling along a mountain valley road.  Each work provides randomly placed assets and color themes.  Save any frame by pressing DOWN.

metadata.name: Aurora At Mount St. Matrice #33
metadata.description:
At the gateway of waking and sleep, warmed by a molten heart; into the arms of night - be bathed by her falling hair.

Process: Forged in Hydra.

🌐 A note on rarity and variety: 

Although there are many variations possible within this piece, they are on the subtler side.

As this is a highly temporal piece, these variations ask you to dive into the experience of the piece in order to fully appreciate them. Please proceed bearing this in mind.

Experiment with the aspect ratio of this piece using the ‘open live’ function below the viewport - it can be enjoyed elastically [as with my previous works here]. A larger frame provides for a deeper experience.

As with a handful of my works, an instance of .blend() is used in this piece, and does cause some slight thinning and dimming to the preview capture. Once more, this still preview is to be considered a skeletal scan of a moment within this piece.
